Class FileUtils.ListFileVisitor

    protected static class FileUtils.ListFileVisitor

    Implementation of FileVisitor to build the list of files based on the glob expression of the file path.

    • Constructor Detail

      • FileUtils.ListFileVisitor

        public FileUtils.ListFileVisitor(List<Path> fileList,
                         PathMatcher pathMatcher,
                         int pathMatcherStartIndex,
                         FileVisitor<? super Path> visitor,
                         FileUtils.FileFilter fileFilter)
        Constructs FileVisitor implementation object.
        Parameters:
        fileList - is the list of files, which patched wild card in glob syntax. This list object is not null in the case if client invokes listFiles method. If it is null then matched file path is not stored. It means that client has called walkFileTree method and provided it's own FileVisitor implementation. NOTE that custom FileVisitor implementation is invoked from this visitor and only for matched paths.
        pathMatcher - is path matcher, which is built based on wild card created by splitPathToBaseDirAndWildcard method.
        pathMatcherStartIndex - is an index of the first path name element, which is start of wild card.
        visitor - is FileVisitor, which is provided by the caller of walkFileTree method. listFiles method passes null.
        fileFilter - is FileFilter implementation object for filter files further after the match. If it's null then all matched files are considered.
        See Also:
        SimpleFileVisitor, FileVisitor
